.TH "ishtp_send_msg" 9 "ishtp_send_msg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ishtp_send_msg \- Send ishtp message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ishtp_send_msg
.BI "(struct ishtp_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct ishtp_msg_hdr *hdr "  ","
.BI "void *msg "  ","
.BI "void(*ipc_send_compl)(void *) "  ","
.BI "void *ipc_send_compl_prm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
ishtp device
.IP "hdr" 12
Message header
.IP "msg" 12
Message contents
.IP "ipc_send_compl" 12
completion callback
.IP "ipc_send_compl_prm" 12
completion callback parameter
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Send a multi fragment message via IPC. After sending the first fragment
the completion callback is called to schedule transmit of next fragment.
.SH "RETURN"
This returns IPC send message status.
